  <name>NextGroove</name>
  <summary>Linux client for Nextcloud Music</summary>
  <description>
    <p>Nextgroove lets you browse and play songs from your Nextcloud instance (with Nextcloud Music installed).</p>
    <p>Features: </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Connects to a Nextcloud instance of your choice via normal API tokens (does not use subsonic/ampache endpoints but the Nextcloud ones</li>
      <li>Can select music from an album view (most recent first), a full list of songs in the collection, or playlists.</li>
      <li>Can select albums, playlists or individual songs from either to the queue.</li>
      <li>Basic MPRIS support allowing to be controlled via common controls and shortcuts.</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

  <developer id="net.rosebirch">
    <name>Dean Birch</name>
  </developer>

